  "Automatic transfers to savings help because they:": "",
  "Are tax-deductible contributions without accounting for additional influences": "",
  "Remove the temptation to spend first, making saving a habit rather than a monthly decision": "",
  "Are required by banks, as conventional savings theory would suggest": "",
  "Earn higher interest rates, based on conventional assumptions about savings": "",
  "Automation leverages behavioral psychology. When savings are transferred automatically before you see the money, you adjust spending to what remains. This makes saving effortless and consistent.": "",
  "A common mistake is using the emergency fund for:": "",
  "Essential car repairs to get to work": "",
  "Covering a job loss for several months": "",
  "Non-emergencies like vacations, holiday shopping, or sale items": "",
  "Paying unexpected medical bills": "",
  "Emergency funds should be reserved for genuine emergencies: job loss, medical expenses, essential repairs. Dipping into the fund for wants (vacations, sales, gifts) depletes protection against real crises.": "",
  "What is a 'financial runway'?": "",
  "Your credit limit across all cards": "",
  "The distance between your home and workplace": "",
  "The speed at which you earn money": "",
  "The number of months you can survive without income using your savings and emergency fund": "",
  "Financial runway is calculated by dividing your total liquid savings by your monthly essential expenses. An $18,000 emergency fund with $3,000/month expenses gives a 6-month runway before money runs out.": "",
  "What is a high-yield savings account (HYSA)?": "",
  "A stock market investment account with high returns regardless of prevailing conditions in practice": "",
  "A retirement account with tax benefits based on the conventional understanding of how accounts processes interact in practice": "",
  "A savings account, often at online banks, offering significantly higher interest rates than traditional savings accounts while maintaining FDIC insurance and liquidity": "",
