  "Target: $2,800 times 6 = $16,800. Current savings: $5,000. Gap: $16,800 - $5,000 = $11,800 needed. At $400/month: $11,800 / $400 = 29.5, approximately 30 months to reach the full 6-month emergency fund.": "",
  "Marcus puts $500/month into a high-yield savings account earning 4.5% APY for 2 years. Approximately how much will he have, and how much of that is interest earned?": "",
