  "Twin sisters Amy and Beth both have $3,000/month in essential expenses. Amy keeps her 6-month fund ($18,000) in a checking account at 0.01% APY. Beth keeps hers in a HYSA at 4.5% APY. Over 5 years (assuming the funds stay fully intact), how much more interest does Beth earn than Amy?": "",
